requirement: The system shall compute the required fuel for propulsion using the equation: required fuel = (mass multiplied by the exponential of the required delta v, divided by Isp, multiplied by 9.81) minus mass.
focus_element:

    <constrainedElement xmi:idref="_18_0_2_1a82048c_1420249021691_321590_46892"/>
    <specification xmi:type="uml:OpaqueExpression" xmi:id="_18_0_2_1a82048c_1420249021707_742939_46919">
      <body>required fuel = (mass * exp(required delta v)/Isp*9.81) - mass</body>
    </specification>
  </ownedRule>

requirement: The Solar Array Sizing Model shall compute the solar array size by dividing the required power by the product of the solar cell power density and the solar array efficiency.
focus_element:
<packagedElement xmi:type="uml:Class" xmi:id="_18_0_2_1a82048c_1420249367794_727354_47148" name="Solar Array Sizing Model">
  <ownedRule xmi:type="uml:Constraint" xmi:id="_18_0_2_1a82048c_1420249367794_409220_47174">
    <constrainedElement xmi:idref="_18_0_2_1a82048c_1420249367794_727354_47148"/>
    <specification xmi:type="uml:OpaqueExpression" xmi:id="_18_0_2_1a82048c_1420249367794_493155_47175">
      <body>area = required power / (capacity * efficiency)</body>
    </specification>
  </ownedRule>

requirement: The system shall compute the required power by summing the average required power multiplied by the time in eclipse divided by the power system efficiency in eclipse and the average required power multiplied by the time in daylight divided by the power system efficiency in daylight, then dividing the result by the percent time in daylight.
focus_element:
<packagedElement xmi:type="uml:Class" xmi:id="_18_0_2_1a82048c_1420311873198_361556_47775" name="Effective Power Need Analysis Model">
  <ownedRule xmi:type="uml:Constraint" xmi:id="_18_0_2_1a82048c_1420311873214_660420_47801">
    <constrainedElement xmi:idref="_18_0_2_1a82048c_1420311873198_361556_47775"/>
    <specification xmi:type="uml:OpaqueExpression" xmi:id="_18_0_2_1a82048c_1420311873214_672595_47802">
      <body>required power = ((avg rev power * time in eclipse / efficiency in eclipse) + (avg rev power * time in daylight / efficiency in daylight)) / percent time in daylight</body>
    </specification>
  </ownedRule>
  <ownedAttribute xmi:type="uml:Port" xmi:id="_18_0_2_1a82048c_1420249928459_396878_47353" name="avg rev power" visibility="private" aggregation="composite"/>
  <ownedAttribute xmi:type="uml:Port" xmi:id="_18_0_2_1a82048c_1420249749113_615930_47302" name="percent time in eclipse" visibility="private" aggregation="composite"/>
  <ownedAttribute xmi:type="uml:Port" xmi:id="_18_0_2_1a82048c_1420250067605_633303_47375" name="power system efficiency in eclipse" visibility="private" aggregation="composite"/>
  <ownedAttribute xmi:type="uml:Port" xmi:id="_18_0_2_1a82048c_1420311978022_690990_47885" name="power system efficiency in daylight" visibility="private" aggregation="composite"/>
  <ownedAttribute xmi:type="uml:Port" xmi:id="_18_0_2_1a82048c_1420312005578_353534_47888" name="required power" visibility="private" aggregation="composite"/>
</packagedElement>
